<i>bound noun</i>: 법 [법] <i>noun</i>: 행태 [행태], 행실 [행실], 행세 [행세], 행동거지 [행동거지], 품행 [품ː행], 습성 [습썽], 버르장머리 [버르장머리], 몸가짐 [몸가짐], 거동 [거ː동] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>bound noun</i><br>
<dt>법 [법]</dt><br>
<dd>1. way</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일을 하는 방법이나 방식.</dd><br>
<dd>A bound noun meaning a method or rule.</dd><br>
<dd>2. right behavior</dd><br>
<dd>마땅히 해야 하는 바른 행동.</dd><br>
<dd>A bound noun meaning a proper behavior that a person is expected to show.</dd><br>
<dd>3. rule</dd><br>
<dd>정해진 사실이나 규칙.</dd><br>
<dd>A bound noun meaning a definite fact or rule.</dd><br>
<dd>4. behavior; habit</dd><br>
<dd>일정하게 하는 행동이나 습관.</dd><br>
<dd>A bound noun meaning a habitual behavior or habit.</dd><br>
<dd>5. beop</dd><br>
<dd>앞말의 내용이 당연함을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A bound noun indicating that the preceding proposition is reasonable.</dd><br>
<dd>6. beop</dd><br>
<dd>앞말의 동작이나 상태가 나타날 가능성이 있음을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A bound noun indicating that the action or state mentioned in the preceding statement is likely to occur.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>행태 [행태]</dt><br>
<dd>behavior; conduct; act; deed</dd><br>
<dd>행동하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>The way one behaves.</dd><br>
<dt>행실 [행실]</dt><br>
<dd>behavior; conduct; deed</dd><br>
<dd>실제 겉으로 드러나는 행동.</dd><br>
<dd>One's actual behavior revealed outwardly.</dd><br>
<dt>행세 [행세]</dt><br>
<dd>1. behavior; demeanor; deed</dd><br>
<dd>세상에서 사람이 마땅히 해야 할 일을 행함. 또는 그런 태도.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of doing what one is expected to do as a human being in the world; or such an attitude.</dd><br>
<dd>2. pretending; pretense; posing; acting</dd><br>
<dd>사실은 그렇지 않은 사람이 어떤 당사자인 것처럼 꾸미어 행동함. 또는 그런 태도.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of faking one's identity, passing oneself off as someone else; or such an attitude.</dd><br>
<dd>3. behavior; attitude</dd><br>
<dd>사람들 사이에 어울려 살아가면서 행동함. 또는 그런 태도.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of behaving in a group; or such an attitude.</dd><br>
<dt>행동거지 [행동거지]</dt><br>
<dd>behavior; conduct; deed</dd><br>
<dd>몸을 움직여서 하는 모든 행동.</dd><br>
<dd>All the actions done by moving one's body.</dd><br>
<dt>품행 [품ː행]</dt><br>
<dd>conduct; behavior; demeanor</dd><br>
<dd>품성과 행실.</dd><br>
<dd>One's personality and behavior.</dd><br>
<dt>습성 [습썽]</dt><br>
<dd>1. habit</dd><br>
<dd>습관처럼 굳어져 버린 성질.</dd><br>
<dd>A quality that has become a habit.</dd><br>
<dd>2. behavior</dd><br>
<dd>같은 종류의 동물에서 공통되는 생활 방식이나 행동 양식.</dd><br>
<dd>A common lifestyle or behavioral pattern among the same type of animal.</dd><br>
<dt>버르장머리 [버르장머리]</dt><br>
<dd>behavior</dd><br>
<dd>(속된 말로) 버릇.</dd><br>
<dd>(slang) Manners.</dd><br>
<dt>몸가짐 [몸가짐]</dt><br>
<dd>behavior; conduct; demeanor</dd><br>
<dd>몸을 보살피거나 가꾸거나 움직이는 태도.</dd><br>
<dd>The way one behaves or takes care of his/her body.</dd><br>
<dt>거동 [거ː동]</dt><br>
<dd>behavior; conduct</dd><br>
<dd>몸을 움직임. 또는 그러한 태도나 행동.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of moving one's body, or such an attitude or behavior.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>